===Noun===
''''''ionization''''''
''*reaction''
#{{chemistry}} or {{physics}} any [[process]] that leads to the [[dissociation]] of a [[neutral]] [[atom]], [[molecule]] or other [[species]] into [[ion]]s; the [[state]] of being [[ionized]]
''*energy''
#{{chemistry}} or {{physics}} the energy required to take a neutral atom and remove an electron. Measured in Kilo Joules kJ. It increases going right and increases going up the periodic table.(Fluorine having the most and Francium having the least)

